DATA CLOUD
Set Up a Marketing Cloud Engagement Connection in Data Cloud

After you create your Data Cloud instance, control the scope of data ingestion and activation from Marketing Cloud Engagement and other sources. Before integrating with Data Cloud, make sure that your Engagement user’s default business unit (BU) is set to the Enterprise ID (EID). Set up your data sources to tell Data Cloud where to pull data from, also known as ingest, for data mapping and segments. Data Cloud supports only Engagement Enterprise 2.0 account connections.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
USER PERMISSIONS
NEEDED
To connect to an Engagement account:	Administrator AND Engagement Administrator Roles must be assigned to the Engagement account user.
NOTE If you set up an Engagement connection before the Spring ‘22 release, skip to step 13 to enable the BU aware integration between Data Cloud and Engagement.
From Setup, click Data Cloud Setup.
Under Configuration, click Marketing Cloud.
To provide your Engagement credentials for authentication, click Manage.
Enter the Engagement username and password.
IMPORTANT We highly recommend using a dedicated Marketing Cloud API user account for integration with Data Cloud to prevent disruptions to your service. If your password expires, activations fail to publish new or updated segments to Engagement until the password is updated. A Marketing Cloud API user's password doesn’t expire.
To enable the channels so that Data Cloud can pull in data, click Manage for Setup bundles to ingest into Data Cloud.
If you don’t want to ingest data from Engagement, click Skip. The available channels in the connected Engagement instance are highlighted.
To enable the highlighted channels so that Data Cloud can pull in data using the Data Cloud Starter Bundles, click Start.
Data bundle sources appear. Use data bundles to quickly and easily create multiple data streams to ingest system-owned data from Engagement. You can manually add more data extensions afterward.
Data Cloud creates a set of automation’s and automation activities in Automation Studio to support data ingest. These automation’s transfer data between the two products. Don’t alter or edit these activities.
To select which business units to ingest data from, click Manage.
From Setup, use the arrows (1) to select the business unit name to add, remove, or move.
The top-level business unit is preselected and can’t be deselected because all subscriber data for the email channel is at that level.
When you select a new business unit, Data Cloud ingests only 90 days of historical data for the business unit.
Click Save.
To enable business unit mapping, this step is required.
To select which business units to activate segments to, click Manage.
Use the arrows to add or remove business units in Selected business units.
You can select any number or combination of business units independent of the BUs selected for ingest.
To automatically map Engagement subscriber data to the Affiliation Data Model Object (DMO), enable Allow Profile Business Unit Mapping Data.
Enabling Allow Profile Business Unit Mapping Data is permanent and can’t be undone. The new SFMC Subscriber BU Mapping Data Stream is created and mapped to the Affiliation DMO. Data can take up to 24 hours to appear in the Affiliation DMO. Until data is ingested into the Affiliation DMO, activations are sent to Engagement as shared data extensions. After successful ingestion, activations are sent as data extensions automatically. Since the SFMC Subscriber BU Mapping Data Stream gets a full refresh one time a day, view the refresh history for the latest status details.
Map other data to the Affiliation DMO.
Create a relationship between the Party field of the Affiliation DMO and the Individual Id field of the Individual DMO with the cardinality of ManyToOne.
Create a data stream and map data to the Affiliation DMO.
Affiliation DMO Fields
FIELD LABEL	FIELD API LABEL	DESCRIPTION	MAPPING REQUIREMENTS
Affiliation ID	ssot__Id__c	Unique value for each individual.	Required
Party	

ssot__PartyId__c

	

Information about the individual.

The default mapping is to the Engagement Subscriber Key field.

	Required
Affiliated To	ssot__AffiliatedTo__c	

Information about the business unit. For example, brand or region.

Default mapping is to the Engagement MID.

This field ensures activations are sent to the right business unit in Engagement.

	Required
Affiliation Type	ssot__AffiliationType__c	Type or category of the affiliation. For example, product category or other granular details.	Optional
